// YouthTagRugby.astro — non-contact youth rugby entry-point section
---

<section class="section youth-section" id="youth">
  <p class="section-label">Spotsylvania Youth Rugby</p>
  <h2 class="section-title">Youth <em>Tag Rugby</em></h2>
  <p class="section-body">
    Spotsylvania Youth Rugby is beginning with a simple goal: introduce
    elementary and middle school students to rugby through safe, non-contact
    play. Spotsylvania Tag Rugby is the first youth entry point, helping
    players learn running, passing, support, spacing, teamwork, and tag defense
    in an age-appropriate format.
  </p>

  <div class="interest-note youth-note">
    <div>
      <h3>Schools first</h3>
      <p>
        The first strategy is to work with local PE teachers to bring rugby
        activities into schools during April and May, followed by summer play
        opportunities for interested families.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h3>Non-contact by design</h3>
      <p>
        No tackling. No scrums. No rucks. No mauls. Just movement, teamwork,
        courage, and fun.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <a href="#interest" class="btn-primary youth-cta">Join the Youth Rugby Interest List</a>
</section>
